               <p>JOHN BLAKEWAY. I am a <rs id="t18300916-109-viclabel580" type="occupation">wine-merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-109-victim1003 t18300916-109-viclabel580"></join>, and live in Mark-lane. On the 10th of September, about four or five o'clock in the afternoon, I was on <placeName id="t18300916-109-crimeloc581">London-bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-109-crimeloc581" type="placeName" value="London-bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300916-109-crimeloc581" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-109-off578 t18300916-109-crimeloc581"></join> - I had just used my handkerchief, and placed it in my outside coat pocket - when I felt a pull at the pocket and found it was gone, I turned round, saw the prisoner running off, seized him, and charged him with taking my handkerchief; I shook him - his coat opened, and it fell from under his coat behind his back; an officer came up and secured him - the handkerchief has my initials on it; he appeared in great distress.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-109-person1004">
                  SAMUEL 
                  BOWLER
               <interp inst="t18300916-109-person1004" type="surname" value="BOWLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-109-person1004" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-109-person1004" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am warder of London-bridge. I was at the foot of the bridge - I saw a crowd run across, and the prosecutor charged the prisoner with stealing his handkerchief, which he delivered to me; I searched, but found nothing on him; he begged the prosecutor not to hurt him, as it was his first offence; he is not known at the offices at all.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I throw myself on the mercy of the Court.</p>
               <p>
